<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-5752] Thrift tables are not supported from CqlPagingInputFormat</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5752</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;CqlPagingInputFormat inspects the system schema to generate the WHERE clauses needed to page &quot;wide rows,&quot; but for a classic Thrift table there are no entries for the &quot;default&quot; column names of key, column1, column2, ..., value so CPIF breaks.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12657535">CASSANDRA-5752</key>
            <summary>Thrift tables are not supported from CqlPagingInputFormat</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
