                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13707451" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 12 Jul 2013 22:10:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was fixed Cassandra-side for 2.0 in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5702&quot; title=&quot;ALTER RENAME is broken in trunk&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-5702&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-5702&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; but the fix was pretty heavyweight and backporting to 1.2.x is not an option.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IMO the right fix for 1.2 is to call CFDefinition.get&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Key,Column,Value&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;Id methods the way the CQL parser does.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;/cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=iamaleksey&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;iamaleksey&quot;&gt;iamaleksey&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=pkolaczk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;pkolaczk&quot;&gt;pkolaczk&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13710195" author="alexliu68" created="Tue, 16 Jul 2013 20:36:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for 1.2 branch is attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13710407" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 16 Jul 2013 22:59:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;-1 on using the exception for control flow; looks like the thrift logic should be merged w/ retrieveKeys.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, please use modern logging API instead of string concatenation; see b2daab711cd8dc03afb39a6464f21325ba0193ee&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13711688" author="alexliu68" created="Wed, 17 Jul 2013 21:58:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;5752-1-1.2-branch.txt is attached. It doesn&apos;t use exception any more&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13715500" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 22 Jul 2013 18:28:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When do we expect partitionBoundColumns to be empty after a non-empty schema_columnfamilies resultset?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13723030" author="alexliu68" created="Mon, 29 Jul 2013 21:57:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If the key_aliases return as string [], the partitionBoundColumns size is zero. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13724311" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 30 Jul 2013 19:41:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;But you&apos;re checking for key_aliases being null earlier.  Which is it going to be?  Both checks should not be necessary.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, I think the &lt;tt&gt;rows.size()==0&lt;/tt&gt; check is bogus; there should always be an entry in schema_columnfamilies.  If there isn&apos;t, falling back to describe_columnfamilies isn&apos;t going to help.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13725731" author="alexliu68" created="Wed, 31 Jul 2013 21:22:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;5752-2-1.2-branch.txt is attached to clean up the code as suggested. It also includes the fix for CqlRecordWriter.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13725823" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 31 Jul 2013 23:21:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to 1.2 only. (In 2.0 the system schema include the required information for Thrift tables, as mentioned above.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
